data.text:
Five potential brides for Emperor Franz Joseph:

♥ 1) Princess Anna of Prussia (1836-1918).- She met Franz Joseph in 1852 and he fall in love with her. The young Emperor was unable to marry her due to political reasons and she finally married in 1853 Prince Frederick William of Hesse-Kassel, who was already widowed of his first beloved wife, Grand Duchess Alexandra Nicholaevna (aka Adini).

♥ 2) Princess Sidonie of Saxony (1834-1862).- Another of the candidates to marry Franz Joseph but he did not feel interested on her. She died unmarried at the age of 27 after an illness.

♥ 3) Archduchess Elisabeth Franziska (1831-1903).- She was already a widow and mother of a little girl when her cousin, Emperor Franz Joseph fall in love with her in 1853. The Archduchess Sophie, mother of the Emperor, refused this marriage because her dislike of the Hungarian branch of the family, to which Elisabeth Franziska belonged. She remarried in 1854 with Archduke Karl Ferdinand.

♥ 4) Duchess Helene in Bavaria (1834-1890).- She was expected to marry Franz Joseph and they met at Bad Ischl at the summer of 1853. He did not chose her as his bride as was expected. She married in 1858 Maximilian, hereditary Prince of Thurn and Taxis and had a happy marriage.

♥ 5) Duchess Elisabeth in Bavaria (1837-1898).- She accompanied her older sister, Helene, to Bad Ischl but when Franz Joseph saw her, he fall in love with Sissi and began courting her instead of her sister. Despite the disagreement of Archduchess Sophie to the match, Franz Joseph was determined to marry Sissi and finally they got married in April 24th, 1854. Unfortunately, it was not a happy marriage.
